<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-28T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="325" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/5009: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-28T19:00:00+03:00">August 28, 1936—7
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 28—6:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>536. I have been officially informed that a band of some 1500
                                Ethiopians attacked the local aerodrome night before last but were
                                defeated. Ethiopian casualties were about 200 while the Italian
                                native troops lost 15 killed and about 40 wounded.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>